  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n## Current behaviour\r\n\r\nCurrently, an imported remapping applies globally. e.g. the following happens\r\n```console\r\n$ forge init\r\n$ mkdir src/ds-test && touch src/ds-test/MyDsTest.sol\r\n$ echo 'import \"ds-test/MyDsTest.sol\";' > src/Contract2.sol\r\n$ forge build\r\n  (...) Failed to resolve file: \"(...)/lib/forge-std/lib/ds-test/src/MyDsTest.sol\": No such file or directory (os error 2).\r\n        Check configured remappings.\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is manageable with 1 level of dependency but will cause surprises with nested dependencies.\r\n\r\n## Suggestion\r\n\r\nOnly apply the remapping when compiling files of the imported dependency (I don't know how forge invokes `solc`, maybe that's not an option). Optionally also rewrite deep imports (like `import dependency/remapped_dir/Contract.sol` from the root level.",
