    "body": "Yes sorry, fixed version:\r\n\r\n```console\r\n$ forge init\r\n$ mkdir ds-test && touch ds-test/MyDsTest.sol\r\n$ echo 'import \"ds-test/MyDsTest.sol\";' > src/Contract2.sol\r\n$ forge build\r\n```\r\n\r\nYou'll get a warning if you rename `ds-test` to something else but it will work.\r\n\r\nMaybe more realistically, in my actual case the dependency had a remapping like `src/...=...`, which clashed one level above. It's also easy to imagine remappings like `utils/=...` being used both in a dependency and in an importing package.\r\n",
